  <summary>2/19/1987--Introduced.
Amends the Perishable Agricultural Commodities Act of 1930 to make it unlawful to fail to mark any perishable agricultural commodity as to its State, country, or region of origin. Increases the penalty from $2,000 to $50,000 for such labeling or misrepresentation violations.</summary>
